1.5 cup All-Purpose Flour
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
2 unit(s) Sour Cream
3 tsp Baking Powder
¼ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
7 g Chives
¼ tsp Salt*
1 tsp Sugar*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 425°F. Wash and dry all produce. Thinly slice the chives. Whisk together mayo, sour cream, chives, cheese, baking powder, 3 tbsp water, 1/4 tsp salt and 1 tsp sugar in a large bowl. Stir in flour until just combined. Using your hands, press dough together into a loose ball. Flatten dough and press into a 1-inch thick disc.

Cut the biscuit disc into 8 equal wedges. (NOTE: you will have 16 wedges for 4 ppl.)Transfer biscuits to a parchment-lined baking sheet. Bake in the middle of the oven, until puffed up and golden, 10-12 min.

Divide the biscuits between plates. Halve biscuits and brush with butter if desired.